<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF108-846-516  </DOCNO><DOCID>08 846 516.andM;</DOCID><JOURNAL>PC Week  Sept 17 1990 v7 n37 p4(1)* Full Text COPYRIGHT Ziff-Davis Publishing Co. 1990.andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>BIOS woes stall September debut of 486 PS/2 line. (introduction of80486-based IBM PS/2 microcomputers delayed until mid-Oct 1990 )</TITLE><AUTHOR>Sexton, Tara.andM;</AUTHOR><DESCRIPT>Company:   International Business Machines Corp. (product development).andO;Ticker:    IBM.andO;Product:   IBM PS/2 (Microcomputer) (product development).andO;Topic:     MicrocomputersBIOSDefectsProduct DelayPlanning.andM;</DESCRIPT><TEXT>BIOS Woes Stall September Debut Of 486 PS/2 LineandM;IBM has delayed the introduction of its 486-based PS/2s until mid-October,according to sources close to and inside the company.andM;The announcement of the PCs, originally scheduled for Sept. 25, was postponedafter IBM engineers discovered problems performing file transfers under OS/2on the unreleased 486-based desktop Model 90 and the tower-style Model 95,sources said.andM;The BIOS problem, which has been identified and is being fixed, can slowperformance considerably, according to an IBM engineer who asked to remainanonymous.andP;  The problem causes large OS/2 file transfers to monopolize themachine, preventing it from performing other tasks while the file transfer istaking place, he said.andM;&quot;File transfer is an important capability in a server.andP;  Announcing themachines with this problem could be fatal,&quot; said one source familiar with thenew PS/2s.andM;IBM officials last week confirmed they had postponed an announcement toperform additional quality-control testing and to increase productionvolumes.andP;  They declined to provide further details on the unannouncedproducts.andM;&quot;We wouldn't go with a product until exhaustive quality testing had beenperformed and there was a sufficient supply,&quot; said Shelia Shanahan, an IBMspokeswoman in White Plains, N.Y.andM;The new PS/2s feature native 486 microprocessors in 25MHz and 33MHz models,sources said.andP;  The October announcement is also expected to include the debutof OS/2 version 1.3, a 386SX-based diskless workstation and possibly IBM'slong-awaited new laptop line, sources said.andO;</TEXT></DOC>